  "market_context": "On the TSLA daily chart, price swept previous swing lows into a gap and formed a V-shape reversal off a bullish order block, resuming the higher-time-frame uptrend with two swing highs above acting as draw on liquidity targets.",
  "key_observation": "Monday printed a bearish expansion candle opposing the range, then Tuesday produced an aggressive candle 2 closure with a continuation through the down-close series, confirming the weekly low and setting up a classic expansion profile higher.",
  "analysis_steps": [
    "Step 1: Established higher-time-frame context on the daily — identified the sweep of previous lows into a gap and the V-shape reversal paired with a bullish order block, confirming a retracement (not reversal) within the uptrend.",
    "Step 2: Marked two swing highs above as draw-on-liquidity targets, noting decent separation between them.",
    "Step 3: Let Monday play out — its bearish expansion close meant the low of the week could not yet be anticipated, so waited for another day.",
    "Step 4: On Tuesday, observed an aggressive candle 2 closure that also closed through the series of down-close candles, allowing anticipation that the weekly low had formed.",
    "Step 5: Dropped to the hourly time frame to confirm a change in the state of delivery on the Tuesday sweep and closure.",
    "Step 6: With confirmation, looked for Wednesday continuation higher, which printed as expected.",
    "Step 7: Since Wednesday closed as a continuation (not a reversal candle), anticipated Thursday continuation, which also delivered higher into the daily swing-high targets.",
    "Step 8: Avoided trading Friday since three expansion days had already hit the higher-time-frame objectives."
  ],
  "outcome": "Wednesday and Thursday delivered continuation expansions higher into the marked daily swing-high targets; Friday was skipped as targets were already met.",
  "lessons": "Do not predict which day forms the weekly low — let it form. Confirm with a daily candle 2 closure plus a closure through the down-close series, then validate with an hourly change in state of delivery before trading subsequent-day continuations into HTF targets.",
